$ SQL Server: sp_addsrvrolemember
@ sp_addsrvrolemember

`sp_addsrvrolemember` adds a *login* to the set of members of a *fixed server role*.

code {
exec sp_addsrvrolemember @loginname = …, @rolename = …
code }

The procedure might be removed in a future version of → development/databases/SQL-Server. Therefore, `alter server role …` should be used instead.
